      "description": "This E92 M3 is a museum-grade example of the final naturally aspirated M-car. Under the hood, the S65 4.0L V8 remains a mechanical masterpiece, featuring eight individual throttle bodies and an 8,400 RPM redline that delivers linear power delivery across the entire rev range. The longitudinal 6-speed manual transmission provides crisp, short-throw engagement, paired with a variable M differential lock for optimal corner-exit traction. The chassis is impeccably preserved, featuring Electronic Damper Control (EDC) that maintains factory-spec damping rates. Comprehensive preventative maintenance has been performed, including a documented rod bearing replacement and throttle actuator service. The paint depth is consistent across all panels, and the interior leather shows zero bolster wear, reflecting its collector-quality preservation.",
